Overview

This project demonstrates a three-tier architecture on AWS, consisting of:

Presentation Layer (Web) – Hosted on EC2
Application Layer (Backend Logic) – Running on EC2
Database Layer – Hosted on RDS (MySQL)

The architecture is designed with network isolation, security, and scalability concepts, while remaining Free Tier friendly.

🔄 Flow:

User → EC2 (Public Subnet) → RDS (Private Subnet)

🛠️ Services Used
Amazon EC2 – Web & Application server
Amazon RDS – MySQL database
Amazon VPC – Network isolation
Amazon S3 – (Optional static hosting)
Amazon CloudWatch – Monitoring
🌐 Network Design
Custom VPC (10.0.0.0/16)
Public Subnet → EC2 (with Internet Gateway)
Private Subnet(s) → RDS (no public access)
Route Tables configured for controlled access
🔐 Security
EC2 Security Group:
HTTP (80) → Public
SSH (22) → Restricted to personal IP
RDS Security Group:
MySQL (3306) → Allowed only from EC2 Security Group

👉 Ensures secure communication between tiers

